Hello eimhee,

It would appear that resolution of *.imageshack.us was failing for you for a long time.

I'm able to resolve img41.imageshack.us right now, so maybe the solution was for someone to fix their dns configuration. If that happened in time, then the next attempt of each of these urls should have succeeded.

These urls are mostly at attempt ~29. By default heritrix makes 30 attempts and then gives up, so these slow retry cycles were probably almost finished.

This could be seen as an example of why the slow retry cycle is a good idea, if dns was broken for a few hours and then fixed in time for the urls to be crawled successfully.

However, if you're sure you want things to fail fast, you can reduce retryDelaySeconds and/or maxRetries in your heritrix configuration.

Noah
